---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import AudioPlayer from '../components/AudioPlayer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "Photo Album - Arielle the Talking Macaw";
const description = "Original Photo Album content from ParrotSpeech featuring Arielle's communication, images, and audio examples.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navigation slot="navigation" currentPage="photos" />
  
  <article>
    <Breadcrumb currentPage="Photo Album" />

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Photo Album</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="hero-section">
      <div class="hero-image-wrap">
        <img src="/images/Arielle_on_perch_foot_up.jpg" alt="Arielle perched with one foot raised" />
        <p class="photo-credit">Photo by Linda Carpenter</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-captions">
        <p>Do you think I'm left footed?</p>
        <p>Do you want to guess again whether I'm left footed?</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="message-box blue-text">
      <p>
        Arielle transmits a basic message. Her gesture means: "Please pick me up!"
      </p>
      <p>
        She makes herself understood. If her message is misunderstood, or if the response is too slow,
        she vocalizes repeatedly until she gets her way. By chanting "Come up! Come up! Come up!"
        or "Want up! Want up! Want up!" she annoys her companion human and succeeds at obtaining her goal.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="yellow-box">
      <p class="red-large">
        Arielle composed the sentiment expressed on her own ... click "play" to hear her words.
      </p>
      <p class="red-small">
        (<a href="/files/Track_DD2.wav">Click here if player image is missing.</a>)
      </p>
      <p class="red-medium">
        If, after hearing her speech, you are unsure of what Arielle said, the transcription and
        explanation appear in a yellow box near the bottom of this page.
      </p>
      <AudioPlayer src="/files/Track_DD2.wav" autoplay={true} caption="Arielle speech sample" />
    </section>

    <section class="playground-section">
      <figure class="playground-image">
        <img src="/images/image001.png" alt="Arielle at a playground" />
        <figcaption>&copy; Michael Dalton</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="playground-text blue-text">
        <p>
          One of Arielle's favorite places is the playground at a nearby park. She enjoys climbing
          up and down over the ladder upon which she stands. She often explores the adjacent bridge
          and the climbing towers too.
        </p>
        <p>
          She is especially fond of little children, and she investigates anyone who might be doing
          something interesting near her. From time to time, Arielle perches upon a person's arm if he
          or she expresses interest in her. She has made a great number of friends along our walks
          over nineteen years.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="yellow-box">
      <p class="red-large">Arielle said, "He loves me."</p>
      <p class="red-medium">
        Her words are not taught because she is female and because her owner would not refer to her
        as "he." This an example of a macaw using words in an appropriate fashion. Importantly,
        she expresses a concept of self when she freely refers to herself as "me." Arielle has a
        "Theory of Mind;" she is one of the few nonhuman animals exhibiting consciousness through speech.
        Note than in addition to the other complexities, she has correctly adjusted the verb form to
        match the subject "he."
      </p>
      <p class="red-medium">
        If one contends that Arielle does not understand what she says, then how does one explain her statement?
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="egg-section">
      <h2>Arielle's First Egg</h2>
      <p class="egg-subtitle">(January 2012, Arielle ~20+ yrs.)</p>
      <figure>
        <img src="/images/Arielle_s_Egg_with_scale.jpg" alt="Arielle's first egg with scale" />
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="pinawor-section">
      <h2>Pictures from PINAWOR</h2>
      <p class="pinawor-subtitle">(Writers' Picnic)</p>
      <div class="pinawor-grid">
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/Pinawor_Pix_2005_L_Williams.jpg" alt="PINAWOR 2005" />
          <figcaption>2005</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/Pinawor_Picnic_2006.jpg" alt="PINAWOR 2006" />
          <figcaption>2006</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="book-section">
      <h2>Below are two pictures from the book <em>Another Kind of Mind</em></h2>
      <div class="book-grid">
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/DSC_00981_On_gym_Morningside.jpg" alt="Arielle on gym at Morningside" />
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/DSC_00271-1_On_mailbox_post.jpg" alt="Arielle on mailbox post" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="closing-statement">
      <p>Arielle understands speech and speaks thoughtfully using English words, phrases, and sentences.</p>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 3.2rem;
    color: #663300;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #00cccc;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .hero-section {
    margin: 20px 0 28px;
  }

  .hero-image-wrap {
    max-width: 430px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-image-wrap img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .photo-credit {
    margin-top: 8px;
    color: #cccccc;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .hero-captions {
    margin-top: 18px;
    text-align: center;
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .hero-captions p {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }

  .message-box {
    margin: 22px 0 30px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .blue-text {
    color: #000066;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .yellow-box {
    background: #ffff00;
    padding: 18px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .red-large {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .red-medium {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .red-small {
    color: #ff0000;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .red-small a {
    color: #663300;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .playground-section {
    margin: 34px 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(250px, 420px) 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .playground-image {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .playground-image img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .playground-image figcaption {
    margin-top: 8px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #663300;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .playground-text {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .playground-text p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .egg-section {
    margin: 38px 0 28px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .egg-section h2 {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .egg-subtitle {
    color: #663300;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .egg-section figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .egg-section img {
    max-width: 260px;
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .pinawor-section {
    margin: 36px 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pinawor-section h2 {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .pinawor-subtitle {
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .pinawor-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .pinawor-grid figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .pinawor-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .pinawor-grid figcaption {
    margin-top: 6px;
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .book-section {
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  .book-section h2 {
    text-align: center;
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .book-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .book-grid figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .book-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .closing-statement {
    margin: 26px auto 18px;
    text-align: center;
    color: #663300;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .playground-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .pinawor-grid,
    .book-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2.3rem;
    }

    .hero-captions,
    .playground-text {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    .egg-section h2,
    .pinawor-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
    }
  }
</style>
